No, your ears do not deceive you. Allow me to introduce you to your new favorite car. @samalbertrally stuffed an NA Ferrari V8 into his 2004 Subaru STI!! This thing is absolute insanity and I’m so excited to see it in a few days!
Sam will be competing in the @olympusrally in Shelton WA next weekend, April 22-23!
Olympus will be the third round of the ARA national championship with 80 cars competing!
Olympus is a special rally for me as well! It is my hometown rally. It was the first event I ever competed in back in 2021, and the first event I ever got a class win at. Winning L2WD with @puravidarally last year. 
This year I will be competing in an Ex WRC Prodrive Subaru with @bardharacing !!
Spectator and volunteer info is now available on the Olympus website! Hope to see you all there soon!!

Max attack was the strategy at LSPR. We needed to win the event and the power stage to win the L4WD championship. 
We had a solid lead in class after 13 stages, but it was all for nothing if we didn’t take the power stage. The transit from service to SS14 was the most anxious, excited, and nervous 45 minutes of my life. 
Villikissa was the roughest, slippiest and most technical stage of the rally, and we were supposed to take it at eleven tenths. 
After a massive push we ended up taking the stage win by 3.8 seconds and the championship by 1 point! 
I just posted the full stage to YouTube. 
Link in bio!!

I’ve been trying to think of a caption for the better part of 4 hours now but I just cannot think of anything to say that can describe the last 12 months. 
At the beginning of the year I was unsure about my plans for the season. But then in late January, a few insane opportunities presented themselves. This led to a crazy adventure that I couldn’t have seen coming. Leading me all over North America and putting on enough miles to travel the equator 5.5 times!!
December 2020 was when I tried Co-Driving for the first time on Dirt Rally. Little high school me would believe all that’s happened just 3 years later. Even right-now me is in disbelief at the experiences from this year. 
I spent a few days pulling all the numbers together and it is mind blowing!
I’m very excited to see the adventure that 2024 has in store!
.
.
.
